NORMALIZATION:

1NF:
All attributes are single valued.
So all tables are already in 1 NF.


2NF:

Relations having single-attribute primary keys are automatically in 2NF.

Examples:
EVENT
VENUE
COMMITTEE
ATTENDEE
TICKET
HOSTEL_ROOM
SPONSOR
BUDGET
VOLUNTEER
COMMITTEE_MEMBER

because all non-key attributes depend entirely on their primary key.


We now analyze relations with composite keys.

1. COMMITTEE_SPONSOR
Relation:
COMMITTEE_SPONSOR(
comm_id,
sponsor_id,
amount,
status
)
Primary Key:
(comm_id, sponsor_id)
FD:
(comm_id,sponsor_id)â†’amount,status
Neither:
comm_idâ†’amount
nor
Sponsor_idâ†’amount

Similarly for status.
Therefore:
no partial dependency exists
relation is in 2NF

2. ACCOMMODATION
Relation:
ACCOMMODATION(
attendee_id,
room_id,
check_in_date_time,
check_out_date,
number_of_guests,
amount,
status
)
Primary Key:
(attendee_id, room_id, check_in_date_time)
FD:
(attendee_id,room_id,check_in_date_time)â†’check_out_date,number_of_guests,amount,status

No attribute depends only on:
attendee_id
Room_id
check_in_date_time
or partial subset
Hence:
no partial dependency
relation is in 2NF

3. EVENT_ARTIST
Initial relation:
EVENT_ARTIST(event_id, artist_id)
PK: (event_id,artist_id)
FD: (event_id,artist_id)->  (event_id,artist_id)
Cannot determine artist_id just from event_id and vice versa
Hence already in 2NF.

4. EVENT_JUDGES
Initial relation:
EVENT_JUDGES(event_id, judge_id)

Just like event_artist.
Also already in 2NF.

Conclusion for 2NF
All relations satisfy 2NF because no non-prime attribute depends on only part of a composite key




3NF and BCNF:

ISSUE 1 â€” ARTIST relation
FD:
artist_idâ†’fee
Problem:
Artist fee is not intrinsic to artist.
The fee depends on which event artist performs in
Thus:
(event_id,artist_id)â†’fee is the correct dependency.
Decomposition
Final Relations
ARTIST(artist_id,first_name,middle_name,last_name,email,genre)
and
EVENT_ARTIST(event_id,artist_id,fee)

Justification
This removes semantic redundancy and update anomalies.
Example problem before normalization:
If same artist performs in 2 events with different fees:
Artist A â†’ â‚ą50,000 in event 1
Artist A â†’ â‚ą1,00,000 in event 3
Single fee attribute becomes inconsistent.
Thus decomposition improves consistency.

